@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{B}[· @{BG SHADOW}@{APEN 2}  MatWB 3.0 @{BG HIGHLIGHT}@{APEN 1} Add-on package    @{BG BACKGROUND} ·]@{UB}

 @{B}  ·          @{U}INTRODUCTION@{UU}         · @{UB}

 "Aha!" I thought, upon seeing @{I}another@{UI}
 probably  lame Workbench enhancer  on
 the  Aminet.  I admit,  I  was wrong,
 @{I}very@{UI}  wrong!  Once I saw the  preview
 I was sold.  This was not an ordinary
 WB  enhancer,  no it was an  enhancer
 for an already  incredible  enhancer.
 That did it,  I got to keep my @{"regged" SYSTEM Extras/MagicWBRegistration}
 MagicWB and  recieved  an  @{I}incredible@{UI}
 enhancement   on   top!   Well,   who
 wouldn't   want   that   8).   So   I
 immediately installed it, but I found
 the  package  was  lacking  some real
 cool window patterns. That's how this
 package got started. I converted some
 textures  that  were  sitting  on  my
 harddrive with my  render proggies to
 the MatWB palette.  Then I came along
 some real cool  party graphics  and I
 started  doing some WB patterns  too.

 Well,  here is  the  result.  If  you
 think this  is a  lame package,  then
 you're absolutely right. That's why I
 doubted to release it,  but if you're
 reading  this,  then you know I  took
 the             risk              8|.

 (I  hope none of the graphics artists
 are     too     mad     at     me...)


